@pytest.mark.unit: Unit tests (fast, no external dependencies)

@pytest.mark.tui: TUI tests using Textual framework (requires isolated event loop)

@pytest.mark.browser: Browser integration tests using Playwright (requires Chromium)

@pytest.mark.integration: Integration tests (slower, may require external resources)

@pytest.mark.slow: Slow tests that may take longer to run

@pytest.mark.asyncio: mark the test as a coroutine, it will be run using an asyncio event loop

@pytest.mark.skip_browser(name): mark test to be skipped a specific browser

@pytest.mark.only_browser(name): mark test to run only on a specific browser

@pytest.mark.browser_context_args(**kwargs): provide additional arguments to browser.new_context()

@pytest.mark.no_cover: disable coverage for this test.

@pytest.mark.anyio: mark the (coroutine function) test to be run asynchronously via anyio.

